manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The LGA-115x-mITX offers a superior compact and slim size without compromising performance.

Key Features Superior Lower Profile LGA-115x-mITX has the height clearance of only 27.3 MM, an even lower profile than the stock Intel fan. Unlike the stock model, the thinner size enables it to fit in both Mini ITX & 1U cases. Efficient Cooling Despite the thin size, the LGA-115x-MITX contains a large 80mm fan to deliver effective and uncompromising cooling. Special Heatsink Design Full size CPU contact area provides uniform heat dissipation on the entire top side of your processor. The heat dissipation radiates evenly to all 4 sides allowing cool air to continuously push heat out directly from the top down. Silent Operation Setting the BIOS to silent mode enables the fan to spin at only 1000 RPM. Noise level is low and quiet during normal system operation without sacrificing performance.

HIGH POWER LGA-115x-mITX Overall Dimensions: 91.99 mm (L) x 91.99 mm (W) x 26.95 mm (H) Fan dimensions: 80 mm (L) x 80 mm (W) x 15 mm (H) Heat Sink Material: Aluminum Fan Speed: 1,000 - 3,000 ± 10% Fan Air Flow: 10.23-28.19 CFM ± 10% Fan Air Pressure: 0.79-4.42 mm H₂O ± 10% Fan Noise Levels: 13.9-28.1 dBA Fan Life Expectancy: 40,000 hours Bearing Type: Hydraulic Connector: 4-pin PWM (compatible with 3pin) Net weight: 149g TDP: 85W

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super Quiet Fan
reviews.reviewText: Super quiet and very low profile. You will need to flip your motherboard over to install the pegs into the threaded nuts, as it does not use the push-down plastic CPU fan fasteners. To me this is an advantage as it puts more pressure on the heatsink to the CPU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Product for the Money
reviews.reviewText: Pretty great little heat-sink and fan. Relevant system specs:CPU: I5 3475SMB: EMB-B75ACase: Weird Acrylic "thing" off AliExpressI was looking for a cheap-ish CPU cooler, for a mini build, in a mini case... this did the trick. Great fan and heat-sink and at half the cost of the equivalent Noctua L9.Pros: great fan and heat-sink on a budget. Keeps the processor fairly cool. Idle (doing nothing) ~33C; normal usage (Netflix, Gmail, etc) ~ 40-45C; higher usage (games, etc) 55-60C. Not bad considering the price. I would have liked a few degrees cooler considering this is an "S" series CPU, but not terrible. I could probably knock off a few degrees with a Noctua L9 but at twice the cost and the L9 might not have fit my case, as it is just a touch bigger.Cons: honestly not many. I did notice that the fan is not silent, not overly loud, but not silent. Under load the fan is audible but not to the point of distraction. Oddly, the fan is quieter at a horizontal position than a vertical one... not sure why. The only other con is the coil-whine... yeah it is there; I did hear an audible coil-whine when I first started using this... it went away after about a week, but for a time I thought I was going mad... give it time and the coil-whine dissipates permanently (the whine is from the springs holding the sink to the board, I think).Overall, worth it!Just a note: I have seen reviews say they are using this for I7 CPUs and the like... I personally would not after the temps on my "S" series processor, but for lower watt CPUs, this is a good deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value for the price
reviews.reviewText: This is a good heatsink cooler for the slim form factor PC case. I used this for i5 4th ten CPU, and I had no issues with dissipating heat from the CPU. Fan is very silent and does the job well.The only thing I would mention is that this cooler may not work for some of those slim 1U chassis. This cooler is about 30mm, and then add the height of the motherboard + cpu, so the total height will be around 40mm to 45mm to fit into some 1U chassis.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The Perfect replacement
reviews.reviewText: The most important feature to mention it is the low profile. The perfect fit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars very good low profile heatsink
reviews.reviewText: works great. low profile so fits into a really small case. fan is loud even at quiet fan setting (- 1 star) in the bios but that's because the rpm is still high rather than the sleeves rubbing like "other" product heatsink fans. used a low voltage adapter to reduce the fan speed and set to normal in the bios . wow so quiet now. in normal youtube usage temps run around 36 c @ 1350 RPM with an i3 8100 . so it is good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 9, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great, quiet.
reviews.reviewText: Perfect replacement for the cooling fan in my HP desktop. I couldn't believe it when my 1 year old HP desktop would not boot because it detected a fan problem. Then, HP support couldn't sell me a replacement - they said I should be able to find one online. I'll never buy another HP again. But, after looking at all the specs on the original HP fan and the CPU, I determined that this one should fit. It did and my HP is running again. I guess I'll get a few more miles out of the HP.The fan works great and is quiet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Failed after about 2 years
reviews.reviewText: Worked great for about 2 years and failed. junk and do not buy. Other fans are on the market you can use. I have had fans in pc's last over 10 years and ended up being replaced because i bought a new case. no reason this fan should of failed.

reviews.reviewText: We build small footprint PC's for our business clients. We use these CPU coolers exclusively on our Intel based PC's. We've had zero failures.Great product for your next build.
